best option for cryptography in C++ by offering the tools necessary to implement a range of practical systems, such as TLS protocol, X.509 certificates, modern AEAD ciphers, PKCS#11 and TPM hardware support, password hashing, and post quantum crypto schemes. A Python binding is included, and several other language bindings are available. The library is accompanied by a featureful command line interface.
See the documentation for more information about included features.
Development is coordinated on GitHub and contributions are welcome. If you need help, please open an issue on GitHub.
If you think you have found a security issue, see the security page for contact information.@Qubuhub
